cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.DM, cs.CC

Reasoning: The paper deals with the computational complexity of subgraph detection problems on multi-layer graphs, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several computer science sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper focuses on the algorithmic aspects of the problem. The second likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) since multi-layer graphs are motivated by real-world problems involving entities and their relationships. The third likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) since the paper mentions community detection, which is a common task in machine learning. The fourth likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) since the paper deals with graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The fifth likely category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity) since the paper analyzes the computational (in)tractability of the subgraph detection problems.
